"{\"abstract\":\"Explicitly exploring the semantics of a relation is significant for high-accuracy relation extraction, which is, however, not fully studied in previous work. In this paper, we mine the topic knowledge of a relation to explicitly represent the semantics of this relation, and model relation extraction as a matching problem. That is, the matching score between a sentence and a candidate relation is predicted for an entity pair. To this end, we propose a deep matching network to precisely model the semantic similarity between a sentence-relation pair. Besides, the topic knowledge also allows us to derive the importance information of samples as well as two knowledge-guided negative sampling strategies in the training process. We conduct extensive experiments to evaluate the proposed framework and observe improvements in AUC of 11.5% and max F1 of 5.4% over the baselines with state-ofthe-art performance.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"48579460\",\"name\":\"Haiyun Jiang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48579460\"},{\"authorId\":\"144500933\",\"name\":\"L. Cui\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144500933\"},{\"authorId\":\"40174003\",\"name\":\"Zhe Xu\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/40174003\"},{\"authorId\":\"2089312\",\"name\":\"Deqing Yang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2089312\"},{\"authorId\":\"47740493\",\"name\":\"Jindong Chen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/47740493\"},{\"authorId\":\"48161931\",\"name\":\"C. Li\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48161931\"},{\"authorId\":\"49722247\",\"name\":\"J. Liu\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/49722247\"},{\"authorId\":\"3366523\",\"name\":\"Jiaqing Liang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3366523\"},{\"authorId\":\"47074418\",\"name\":\"C. Wang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/47074418\"},{\"authorId\":\"3011950\",\"name\":\"Y. Xiao